parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump Failure in High Temperatures
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump in high temperatures can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leaving the driver stranded and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails to start in warm or hot weather
the fuel pump does not engage
the engine turns over but does not start
the scooter must be cooled down before it can operate again.
